{"id":14881056,"mediaExerciseId":"2e053a52-210d-4a10-8229-2a699d541d43","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":6002700,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should find the YTM of West Corp. bonds.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We can classify yield to maturity as a return rate. More specifically, yield to maturity is what an investor will earn if he holds the bond until the maturity date when the issuer pays back all the promised interest payments and the amount of the debt written in the contract (principal). We can say that this is a nominal interest rate at the annual level. The best way to calculate yield to maturity is to use a Spreadsheets.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's follow the formula for calculating the price of the bond.\n\n$$\\text{Price}=\\dfrac{\\text{C}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)}+\\dfrac{\\text{C}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{2}}+...+\\dfrac{\\text{C}+\\text{P}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{n}}$$\n\n$C$ - coupon of the bond \n\n$YTM$ - yield to maturity\n\n$P$ - par value\n\n$n$ - time","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":30,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/7f4ce18372a63b85d1333f662f853a06/lateximg_large.png","width":851},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/7f4ce18372a63b85d1333f662f853a06/lateximg.png","width":425}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"We have data that the bond price is 105\\% of the nominal value.\nLet's assume that the nominal value of the bond is \\$1,000. It means:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{bond price}&=105\\%\\times\\$1,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$1050}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The current price of the bond is \\$1050.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/beb8f29369ee41e9da697ccefcacb277/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/beb8f29369ee41e9da697ccefcacb277/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Also, the payments are semiannual. We just need to divide the coupon rate by two because we will get paid twice per year. Also, YTM should be adjusted in the same way. But the period we should multiply by 2. In total, we will get paid not 25 times but 50 because of the semiannual payment.\n\n*Hint: 2 years have passed. That is why we will take 46 periods.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":291,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/6e1ea4e0ae9374b5555e8878751fd2c6/lateximg_large.png","width":864},"regular":{"height":147,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/6e1ea4e0ae9374b5555e8878751fd2c6/lateximg.png","width":432}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's calculate the coupon rate and the coupon value.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{coupon rate}&=\\dfrac{5.3\\%}{2}\\\\[15pt]\n&=2.65\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The coupon rate is 2.65\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":285,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/c28ce378c13c926e8cf8e87f7ce1ae99/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/c28ce378c13c926e8cf8e87f7ce1ae99/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{coupon value}&=\\text{coupon rate}\\times\\text{face value}\\\\[15pt]\n&=2.65\\%\\times\\$1,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$26.5\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The coupon value is \\$26.5.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/8c498fab2a42b7d49528c9124a280e86/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/8c498fab2a42b7d49528c9124a280e86/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's insert all the data in the formula for the bond price.\n\n$$\\$1050=\\dfrac{\\$26.5}{\\text{YTM}+1}+\\dfrac{\\$26.5}{\\left(\\text{YTM}+1\\right)^2}+..+\\dfrac{\\$26.5+\\$1,000}{\\left(\\text{YTM}+1\\right)^{46}}$$\n\n**By using the Spreadsheets, we can find that YTM is 4.93\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":502,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/a986e541dbbf179d3360f9ef14c74c80/lateximg_large.png","width":766},"regular":{"height":253,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/a548cd893fe1a4b96656b40708ddc0b4/a986e541dbbf179d3360f9ef14c74c80/lateximg.png","width":383}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"f132e942-1b46-494f-9b96-a620e7336dee","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":8}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881057,"exerciseName":"8","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fa5b21dc-f94d-4ae8-9644-143e78afefa7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-8-fa5b21dc-f94d-4ae8-9644-143e78afefa7"},{"id":14881058,"exerciseName":"9","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b2b53620-aa5d-45d2-85a5-1c3635d64065","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-9-b2b53620-aa5d-45d2-85a5-1c3635d64065"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881055,"exerciseName":"6","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"950c2961-96ce-463d-a7a5-57818771924c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-6-950c2961-96ce-463d-a7a5-57818771924c"},{"id":14881054,"exerciseName":"5","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e3125d28-379a-4f64-937c-a141db29fe10","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-5-e3125d28-379a-4f64-937c-a141db29fe10"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-editio